#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:28
# header
msgid "### Learner Profiles"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:30
msgid "To teach effectively, you have to know *who* you are teaching. Your audience can be identified in many ways.  Frequently\n"
"people who are hosting a workshop have a specific audience in mind, based on their own experience.  "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:33
msgid "One \"creative\" way to think deeply about the audience for a workshop is to take a few moments to write *learner profiles*.\n"
"Learner profiles have three parts:\n"
"the person's general background,\n"
"the problem they face,\n"
"and how the course will help them.\n"
"One example of a learner profile for a Software Carpentry workshop might be:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:40
# blockquote, which can be cascaded
msgid "> João is an agricultural engineer doing his masters in soil physics."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:41
# blockquote, which can be cascaded
msgid "> His programming experience is a first year programming course using C."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:42
# blockquote, which can be cascaded
msgid "> He was never able to use this low-level programming in his activities,"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:43
# blockquote, which can be cascaded
msgid "> and never programmed after the first year."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:44
msgid ">\n"
"> His work consists of evaluating physical properties of soil samples from different conditions.\n"
"> Some of the soil properties are measured by an automated device that sends logs in a text format to his machine.\n"
"> João has to open each file in Excel,\n"
"> crop the first and last quarters of data values,\n"
"> and calculate an average.\n"
">\n"
"> Software Carpentry will show João how to write shell scripts to count the lines and crop the right range for each file,\n"
"> and how to use R to read these files and calculate the required statistics.\n"
"> It will also show him how to put his programs and files under version control\n"
"> so that he can re-run analyses and figure out which results may have been affected by changes."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_episodes/15-lesson-study.md:57
# blockquote, which can be cascaded
