#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:1
# Front Matter
msgid "---\n"
"layout: page\n"
"title: \"Glossary\"\n"
"---"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:6
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Accessibility**: "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:7
msgid "    Equal access to learning opportunities regardless of learners' physical abilities or other attributes."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:9
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Authentic Task**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:10
msgid "    A task which contains important elements of things that learners would\n"
"    do in real life (i.e. non-classroom situations).  To be authentic, a task should\n"
"    require learners to construct their own answers rather than choose\n"
"    among provided answers, and to work with the same tools and data\n"
"    they would use in real life."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:16
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Chunking**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:17
msgid "    The act of grouping related concepts together so that they can be\n"
"    stored and processed as a single unit."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:20
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Cognitive Load**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:21
msgid "    [Cognitive load][wikipedia-cognitive-load] is the amount of mental\n"
"    effort required to solve a problem.  Cognitive load theory divides\n"
"    this effort into *intrinsic*, *extraneous*, and *germane*, and holds\n"
"    that people learn faster and better when extraneous load is reduced."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:26
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Community of Practice**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:27
msgid "    A self-perpetuating group of people who share and develop a craft or\n"
"    occupation, such as knitters, musicians, or programmers."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:30
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Competent Practitioner**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:31
msgid "    Someone who can do normal tasks with normal effort under normal\n"
"    circumstances.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *novice* and *expert*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:36
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Concept Map**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:37
msgid "    A picture of a mental model in which concepts are nodes in a graph\n"
"    and relationships are (labelled) arcs."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:40
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Deliberate Practice**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:41
msgid "    The act of observing performance of a task while doing it in order to\n"
"    improve ability."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:44
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Diagnostic Power**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:45
msgid "    The degree to which a wrong answer to a question or exercise tells the\n"
"    instructor what misconceptions a particular learner has."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:48
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Educational Psychology**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:49
msgid "    The study of how people learn.\n"
"    <br>"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:52
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Effort-based Praise**: "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:53
msgid "    Providing positive feedback to learners that recognizes and rewards their hard work.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *improvement-based praise* and *performance-based praise*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:57
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Error Framing**: Presenting errors as an integral part of the learning process and using them as teaching opportunities."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:59
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Expert**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:60
msgid "    Someone who can diagnose and handle unusual situations, knows when the\n"
"    usual rules do not apply, and tends to recognize solutions rather than\n"
"    reasoning to them.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *competent practitioner* and *novice*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:66
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Expert Blind Spot**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:67
msgid "    The inability of experts to empathize with novices who are\n"
"    encountering concepts or practices for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:70
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Faded Example**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:71
msgid "    A series of examples in which a steadily increasing number of key\n"
"    steps are blanked out.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *scaffolding*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:76
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Fixed Mindset**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:77
msgid "    The belief that an ability is innate, and that failure is due to a\n"
"    lack of some necessary attribute.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *growth mindset*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:82
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Fluid Representation**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:83
msgid "    The ability to move quickly between different models of a problem."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:85
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Formative Assessment**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:86
msgid "    Assessment that takes place during a lesson in order to give both the\n"
"    learner and the instructor feedback on actual understanding.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *summative assessment*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:91
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Growth Mindset**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:92
msgid "    The belief that ability comes with practice.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *fixed mindset*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:96
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Impostor Syndrome**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:97
msgid "    A feeling of insecurity about one's accomplishments that manifests as\n"
"    a fear of being exposed as a fraud."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:100
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Improvement-based Praise**: "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:101
msgid "    Providing positive feedback to learners that recognizes and rewards improvements they have made.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *effort-based praise* and *performance-based praise*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:105
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Inclusivity**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:106
msgid "    Working actively to include people with diverse backgrounds and needs."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:108
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Inquiry-Based Learning**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:109
msgid "    The practice of allowing learners to ask their own questions, set\n"
"    their own goals, and find their own path through a subject."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:112
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Lateral Knowledge Transfer**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:113
msgid "    The \"accidental\" transfer of knowledge that occurs when an instructor\n"
"    is teaching one thing, and the learner picks up another."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:116
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Learner Profile**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:117
msgid "    A brief description of a typical target learner for a lesson that\n"
"    includes their general background, what they already know, what they\n"
"    want to do, how the lesson will help them, and any special needs they\n"
"    might have."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:122
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Learning Objective**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:123
msgid "    What a lesson is trying to achieve."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:125
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Lesson Study**: "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:126
msgid "    The process in which instructors collaboratively plan lessons,\n"
"    observe each other's teaching, and discuss teaching experiences\n"
"    in order to learn from each other."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:130
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Live Coding**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:131
msgid "    The act of teaching programming by writing software in front of\n"
"    learners as the lesson progresses."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:134
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Long-Term Memory**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:135
msgid "    The part of memory that stores information for long periods of time.\n"
"    Long-term memory is very large, but slow.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *short-term memory*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:140
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Mental Model**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:141
msgid "    A representation of a person's knowledge and thought processes about a topic or domain."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:143
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Minute Cards**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:144
msgid "    A feedback technique in which learners spend a minute writing one\n"
"    positive thing about a lesson (e.g., one thing they've learned) and\n"
"    one negative thing (e.g., a question that still hasn't been answered)."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:148
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Novice**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:149
msgid "    Someone who has not yet built a usable mental model of a domain.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *competent practitioner* and *expert*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:153
# unordered list
msgid "*   **One-Up, One-Down**: "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:154
msgid "    A feedback technique in which learners take turns giving positive and negative feedback without repeating anything that has been said before."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:156
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Participatory Live Coding**"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:157
msgid "	A style of teaching where the instructor [live codes][wikipedia-live-coding] 		\n"
"	and the learners \"code along\"."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:160
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Performance-based Praise**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:161
msgid "    Providing positive feedback to learners that focuses on whether they have attained the correct answer.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *effort-based praise* and *performance-based praise*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:165
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Perseverance**: "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:166
msgid "    The trait of persisting in the face of difficulty."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:168
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Persistent Memory**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:169
msgid "    see *long-term memory*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:171
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Plausible Distractor**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:172
msgid "    A wrong answer to a multiple-choice question that will seem to some students to be correct due to a misconception they hold.\n"
"    <br>\n"
"    See also *diagnostic power*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:176
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Reflective Practice**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:177
msgid "    see *deliberate practice*."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:179
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Scaffolding**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:180
msgid "    Extra material provided to early-stage learners to help them solve problems."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:182
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Short-Term Memory**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:183
msgid "    The part of memory that briefly stores information that can be\n"
"    directly accessed by consciousness."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:186
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Stereotype Threat**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:187
msgid "    A situation in which people feel that they are at risk of being held\n"
"    to stereotypes of their social group."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:190
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Summative Assessment**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:191
msgid "    Assessment that takes place at the end of a lesson to tell whether the\n"
"    desired learning has taken place."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:194
# unordered list
msgid "*   **Working Memory**:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/_extras/glossary.md:195
msgid "    see *short-term memory*."
msgstr ""

