#: instructor-training/index.md:7
msgid "Over the last hundred years,\n"
"researchers have discovered an enormous amount about how people learn\n"
"and how best to teach them.\n"
"Unfortunately,\n"
"much of that knowledge has not yet been translated into common classroom practice, especially at the university level."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:13
msgid "This two-day class has the following overall goals:"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:15
# unordered list
msgid "*   Introduce you to evidence-based best-practices of teaching."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:16
# unordered list
msgid "*   Teach you how to create a positive environment for learners at your workshops."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:17
# unordered list
msgid "*   Provide opportunities for you to practice and build your teaching skills."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:18
# unordered list
msgid "*   Help you become integrated into the [Carpentries]({{ site.carpentries_site }}) community. "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:19
# unordered list
msgid "*   Prepare you to use these teaching skills in teaching [Carpentries]({{ site.carpentries_site }}) workshops."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:21
msgid "Because we have only two days, some things are beyond the scope of this class. We will not be learning:  \n"
"*   How to program in R or Python, use Git or SQL, or any of the other topics taught in Software Carpentry, Data Carpentry, or Library Carpentry workshops. \n"
"*   How to create your own lessons from scratch (although you will have a good start on the principles behind that sort of work if you're inspired to learn more). "
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:25
msgid "*Please fill in [the online application form][application-form] if you wish to take part in this course.\n"
"Priority is given to members of our partner organizations,\n"
"but we run several open-enrollment classes each year as well.*"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:36
# unordered list
msgid "*   All participants in this course are required to abide by our [Code of Conduct][conduct]."
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:37
# unordered list
msgid "*   There are no specific prerequisites for this training,"
msgstr ""

#: instructor-training/index.md:38
msgid "    but participants will benefit from having attended a Data Carpentry or Software Carpentry workshop either as learner or helper\n"
"    so that they are familiar with our teaching techniques and the style of our workshops.\n"
"*   In particular, participants are *not* required to have any specific programming skills\n"
"    (though of course they should know enough about the subjects of one or more of our lessons\n"
"    to be able to teach them)."
msgstr ""

